---
description: Mandatory Python virtual environment isolation
alwaysApply: true
---

# Python venv Mandatory (Highest Priority)

- All Python execution (scripts, tools, tests, installs, TTS/ML pipelines) must run inside a project virtual environment.
- For this repository, the default and preferred environment is `./.venv`.
- Never install Python packages to host/system Python for project tasks.
- Never rely on globally installed Python libraries as a hidden dependency.
- Never use `conda` for project Python steps unless the user explicitly requests a conda-only path.
- Never create extra project-local Python envs (e.g. `.venv-*`) when `./.venv` already exists and is usable.
- If a required package is missing, install it into the active venv only.
- If no venv is active, create/activate one first, then run Python commands.
- Release blocker:
  - if any project Python step was run outside venv, the run is non-compliant and must be redone in venv.
